ide-phenothiazine interaction: report of a case with seizures following myelography." Acta Radiol Diagn (Stockh) 16 (1975): 129-35[3] "Product Information. Omnipaque 180 (iohexol)." Amersham Health, Princeton, NJ.[4] "Product Information. Osmovist 240 (iotrolan)." Berlex Canada Inc, Lachine, QC.[5] "Product Information. Isovue-M-200 (iopamidol)." Bracco Diagnostics Inc, Princeton, NJ.', 1767363024);
